Australian, New Zealand Dollars Weaken After U.S. Equities Futures Slide

-- B y   C a n d i c e   Z a c h a r i a h s
-- 
2011-08-07T22:07:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/australian-new-zealand-dollars-weaken-after-u-s-equities-futures-slide.html
The Australian and  New Zealand 
dollars weakened against the greenback as U.S. equities futures
fell after  Standard & Poor’s  lowered the U.S.’s credit rating.  The Aussie dollar slid to $1.0409 as of 8:05 a.m. in Sydney
from $1.0442 on Aug. 5, while New Zealand’s currency weakened to
83.91 U.S. cents from 84.33 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candice Zachariahs in Sydney at 
 czachariahs2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Garfield Reynolds at 
